c: 39
v: 71
t: "The ones who disbelieve will be driven along to Hell in throngs until, just as they come up to it, its gates will swing open and its keepers will say to them: \"Did not messengers come to you from among yourselves reciting your Lord´s verses to you and warning you about meeting [Him] on this day of yours?\" They will say: \"Of course!\" But the Sentence about torment has still come due for disbelievers"